<%# landing-page: standalone marketing / SEO page (app/views/public), not part of a user's blog %>
<%= content_for :title do %>
  Pagecord – a fresh, modern Blogger alternative
<% end %>

<%= content_for :meta_description do %>
  Blogger made blogging simple. Pagecord is for people who still believe in personal blogging but want a modern way to publish from email, Obsidian, RSS, and their own domain.
<% end %>

<%= content_for :og_image do %>
  <%= dynamic_og_image_for_landing_page(title: "A Modern Blogger Alternative") %>
<% end %>

<div class="md:mt-4 mb-4 md:mb-8 mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4">
  <h1 class="source-serif font-semibold text-center text-4xl md:text-6xl tracking-tight text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200">
    Check out Pagecord – a fresh, modern Blogger alternative
  </h1>

  <div class="md:text-xl text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 flex flex-col gap-y-4 mt-8 md:mt-12">
    <p>
      Blogger helped millions of people start writing online. It made personal publishing feel possible, friendly, and low-pressure.
    </p>
    <p>
      Pagecord is for people who still want that spirit, but want a modern way to keep a personal blog alive: publish from email, Obsidian, the editor, API, or CLI, then let readers follow by RSS or email.
    </p>
    <p>
      Use your own domain, keep your archive, export your work, and avoid turning your blog into another platform feed to manage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="text-center mt-8 mb-4 md:text-xl">
    <%= link_to new_signup_path do %>
      <div class="mt-2 inline-flex font-medium p-4 rounded-xl shadow-sm btn-primary text-xl">Start a Pagecord blog for free</div>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>

<%= render "public/screenshots" %>

<div class="md:mt-4 mb-4 md:mb-8 mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4">
  <section class="my-10 md:my-14 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8">
    <h2 class="source-serif font-semibold text-3xl md:text-4xl tracking-tight text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200">Moving from Blogger</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 md:text-xl text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 flex flex-col gap-y-4">
      <p>
        If you have an existing Blogger archive, you do not need to work it all out before starting. Create a Pagecord blog, try the writing flow, and keep your old site live while you decide what to bring over.
      </p>
      <p>
        Imports are not self-serve yet. If you have an existing blog, <a href="mailto:hello@pagecord.com?subject=Blogger%20Import%20Request" class="home-link">email support</a> and we will look at what is possible.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

<%= render "home/testimonials" %>
